Prof. Nettleship (Journal of Philology XXIX. 35) commenting on the union of luminousness and beauty in Cicero's style remarks on the concluding paragraphs of this speech : “ such a passage...speaks home to us with a living impression of unity and directness which we acknowledge without question. We admire and ask for nothing more.’'
